---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Advertisment Analytics"
	description="google ad analtics"
	pubDate={new Date('March 08 2026')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<div class="photo-gallery">
		<img src="/images/barbers-big-ballin-band.png" alt="Barber's Big Ballin' Band promotional poster" />
		<img src="/images/campaigns-ads.png" alt="Google Ads Campaigns overview" />
		<img src="/images/insights-ads.png" alt="Google Ads Insights dashboard" />
	</div>

	<p>
	As you can see above, that is my digital advertisment for an imagnary band I might set up in the future.
	And here the lackluster analtics for said advertisment.

	</p>
	<p>
		The reason for the name "Barbour's Big Ballin' Band" is that I wanted this band to embody the spirit and elegance of a classic ballroom experience. The name itself is meant to be catchy and memorable while still hinting at the big band style of music we perform.
	</p>
	<p>
		So naturally, my target audience for this advertisement was anybody in need of a big band to play at a ballroom setting. This could apply to a wide variety of events: a wedding, a corporate party, a formal dance, a charity gala, a holiday celebration, and much more. The versatility of a big band makes it an appealing choice for hosts who want to create a sophisticated yet lively atmosphere for their guests.
	</p>
	<p>
		The way I crafted my demographic was largely through the overall look and feel of the advertisement. I intentionally made it appear more polished and mainstream, leaning into a "pop-y" aesthetic and shying away from anything too avant-garde or niche. The goal was to appeal to the widest possible audience rather than a specific subculture of music enthusiasts.
	</p>
	<p>
		There is currently no formal Call to Action in the ad, but ideally it would feature a phone number or booking link so potential clients could easily reach out to hire the band for their upcoming event.
	</p>
	<p>
		My results were unfortunately zero across the board. Part of this is because the ad hasn't been running long enough to gain meaningful traction. However, the bigger issue is that Google ads simply aren't the right platform for this kind of service. The ad received absolutely zero interaction and, frankly, likely came across as untrustworthy to anyone who did see it.
	</p>
	<p>
		If I were to do this again, I would pivot to Instagram or TikTok, where I could incorporate actual audio and video footage of the band performing. Seeing and hearing the band in action would be far more persuasive and help build credibility with potential clients.
	</p>

</Layout>

<style>
	.photo-gallery {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.photo-gallery img {
		width: 100%;
		height: auto;
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
	}
</style>
